WEBVTT

01:00.060 --> 01:03.052
♪♪

01:30.757 --> 01:33.749
♪♪

02:03.999 --> 02:04.999
Penny for them.

02:06.209 --> 02:07.699
They're not worth a penny.

02:07.794 --> 02:11.582
- Oh, come on. I'll pay double.
- Heh. I'd maybe consider triple.

02:11.673 --> 02:12.913
- Triple?
- Yeah.

02:13.008 --> 02:14.794
Tough guy, huh?

02:17.596 --> 02:18.927
Maybe not so tough.

02:19.014 --> 02:23.007
If I want a roller coaster,
I'll take six flags.

02:23.101 --> 02:25.467
Oh, lighten up. It's a vacation, Jack.

02:25.562 --> 02:29.896
Yeah. Sipping rum and coke on a beach
in Bora Bora, now that's a vacation.

02:29.983 --> 02:32.315
We did those. Boring.

02:33.820 --> 02:35.151
"We"?

02:35.238 --> 02:38.730
Me, the kids, you.
It's good all around.

02:39.868 --> 02:44.077
Yeah. It'll be fun.
I just don't like the fact

02:44.164 --> 02:46.496
that this family's become a democracy
all of a sudden.

02:47.876 --> 02:48.996
It was a velvet coup, honey.

02:49.044 --> 02:51.706
Hah - you never noticed.

03:16.488 --> 03:19.480
♪♪

03:30.043 --> 03:31.908
Heaven, Jack.

03:32.003 --> 03:33.789
I've landed in heaven. Thank you.

03:33.880 --> 03:35.120
Hey, Sam.

03:35.215 --> 03:38.173
Uh, so we just landed and, um...

03:38.260 --> 03:40.216
- Mom, where are we?
- Hey, Sam.

03:40.303 --> 03:42.794
We are just outside
of Amboseli Park in Kenya!

03:42.889 --> 03:46.347
Amboseli. Check this place out,
isn't it cool?

03:46.435 --> 03:47.925
It's, like, animals.

03:48.019 --> 03:50.601
Hey, uh, Zoe, Billy.
Guys, say hi to Sam.

03:50.689 --> 03:52.475
- Hi, Sam.
- Hey, Sam. How's it going?

03:52.566 --> 03:55.933
You should be here, yo.
Fucking good!

03:56.027 --> 03:58.313
- Come on, Billy.
- I'm sorry, missus.

03:58.405 --> 04:01.112
We're headed to a lodge

04:01.199 --> 04:03.565
and then we're going, uh,
on safari tomorrow.

04:04.661 --> 04:05.696
I wish you could come.

04:05.787 --> 04:08.870
But, uh... dad. Dad, say hi to Sam.

04:10.000 --> 04:13.083
- Hi, Sam.
- It's so hard, Jack?

04:13.170 --> 04:14.910
Send me a video back, okay?

04:17.339 --> 04:19.171
Hey, I said hi.
- I said hi.

04:25.599 --> 04:28.090
Okay. Uh, asante.

04:28.185 --> 04:29.579
All right. Let's go. Let's go, kids.

04:29.603 --> 04:32.310
Billy, let's go get our car.

04:32.397 --> 04:35.730
- Wait, wait, wait.
- Whoa, whoa.

04:35.817 --> 04:37.432
- Wait.
- What's happening?

04:37.527 --> 04:39.167
I don't know. We're just gonna wait here.

04:48.997 --> 04:51.079
- What are they doing?
- Team lioness.

04:51.166 --> 04:52.997
Anti-poaching unit. All female.

04:55.170 --> 04:56.535
Women soldiers?

04:56.630 --> 04:58.621
- That's badass.
- Yeah. Hm.

04:59.883 --> 05:01.544
Looks like they caught their man.

05:01.635 --> 05:03.876
They say they haven't
lost an elephant in years.

05:03.970 --> 05:06.908
- Wait, wait, those men are poachers?
- They're lucky they're arrested.

05:06.932 --> 05:08.718
Usually, they're shot on sight.

05:08.809 --> 05:11.221
- What?!
- Good. Fuckers.

05:11.311 --> 05:12.497
- Zoe, just...
- That's just an execution.

05:12.521 --> 05:13.521
How is that even legal?

05:13.605 --> 05:16.438
- TIA.
- TIA. "This is Africa."

05:16.525 --> 05:19.813
- Must be your first time here.
- No, no. I've...

05:19.903 --> 05:21.393
I've been to Nairobi before, not...

05:21.488 --> 05:23.695
I mean, this Africa is different. I...

05:23.782 --> 05:27.115
My sightseeing was basically the inside
of corporate boardrooms.

05:27.202 --> 05:29.909
So, uh, what is your business, my friend?

05:29.996 --> 05:32.453
- I work for exxon.
- Ah. Oilman.

05:32.541 --> 05:34.421
- Well, it's more...
- Are you here on vacation?

05:35.544 --> 05:37.205
No, no, no, no. Uh... we... uh...

05:37.295 --> 05:40.287
We help run a community outreach program,

05:40.382 --> 05:42.373
teaching locals how to thrive
off their land.

05:42.467 --> 05:44.207
- Good for you.
- That's great.

05:44.302 --> 05:46.418
That's really cool. Jack, isn't that cool?

05:46.513 --> 05:48.378
It's all right. It's all right.

05:50.809 --> 05:52.765
- Okay, you can now leave.
- Okay.

05:52.853 --> 05:55.206
- Nice meeting you. Nice meeting you.
- Thank you.

05:55.230 --> 05:57.016
- Tia and all that.
- He looked great.

05:57.107 --> 05:58.722
You didn't even know him, Zoe.

05:58.817 --> 06:00.933
This country's gonna eat them alive.

06:07.742 --> 06:09.949
This... is the luxury Africa cruiser?

06:10.036 --> 06:12.652
This is actually the best luxury cruiser.

06:14.374 --> 06:16.490
- I asked for a Mercedes.
- No, sir, just come, come.

06:16.585 --> 06:18.312
- I ordered a Mercedes.
- This is the best cruiser.

06:18.336 --> 06:20.873
This is actually the best vehicle
here in Kenya.

06:20.964 --> 06:23.671
This is the best one for you all.

06:23.758 --> 06:24.838
For your price.

06:26.052 --> 06:27.332
I-I don't even know what to say.

06:27.387 --> 06:28.752
- I like it.
- Come on in.

06:28.847 --> 06:30.178
Come on in. Come on in.

06:30.265 --> 06:32.802
I think she's perfect.
I think we gotta name her.

06:32.893 --> 06:34.884
- Gertrude.
- Gertrude?

06:36.855 --> 06:39.471
- Gertie. Gertie!
- Huh? Gertie?

06:39.566 --> 06:40.601
Hey, does the AC work?

06:40.692 --> 06:43.149
No.. The AC does not work.

06:43.236 --> 06:45.227
Have a lovely holiday.

06:46.364 --> 06:47.364
Bye-bye.

06:50.744 --> 06:52.735
♪♪

07:06.718 --> 07:09.585
How can they not have a paved road
from the airport?

07:09.679 --> 07:10.679
It's a developing nation.

07:10.764 --> 07:13.004
I guess they don't have the money
for that kind of thing.

07:14.267 --> 07:16.132
Wow. Oh, my gosh.
Look, look, look, look.

07:16.227 --> 07:17.808
Wow. Wow. Wow. Look at that.

07:17.896 --> 07:19.636
- Oh, my gosh.
- Aw.

07:20.982 --> 07:22.847
Oh, my god. They're real.

07:22.943 --> 07:25.810
- Look how they run!
- Just some zebras just hangin' out.

07:25.904 --> 07:27.815
- It's amazing.
- Wow.

07:27.906 --> 07:29.612
Welcome to Africa.

07:31.326 --> 07:34.318
♪♪

07:37.832 --> 07:38.662
Wow.

07:38.750 --> 07:41.366
- What have they got behind those gates?
- Here we are.

07:41.461 --> 07:42.461
This is the lodge.

07:42.545 --> 07:45.252
Whoa, this is where we're staying?

07:45.340 --> 07:46.340
Home sweet home.

07:46.424 --> 07:47.834
- Oh, yeah.
- Hello.

07:47.926 --> 07:49.837
- Jambo. Jambo.
- Hello.

07:51.763 --> 07:53.628
- Welcome. Towel?
- Thank you.

07:53.723 --> 07:55.884
Here we go.

07:55.976 --> 07:57.954
- Come on. Thank you.
- Jambo. Jambo.

07:57.978 --> 07:59.843
- Hi.
- Welcome.

07:59.938 --> 08:02.395
Hey. Good to see you, man.

08:02.482 --> 08:05.770
- Wow.
- Jambo.

08:05.860 --> 08:07.851
♪♪

08:24.087 --> 08:26.874
- Huh.
- Oh, look at this view.

08:26.965 --> 08:30.173
- Oh, look at this room. Jack!
- Wow.

08:30.260 --> 08:33.297
- Look at this.
- Huh!

08:33.388 --> 08:36.255
Beautiful.

08:36.349 --> 08:38.149
Yeah, it should be for the price
we paid. Wow.

08:38.183 --> 08:40.971
- Oh, Jack.
- Huh.

08:41.062 --> 08:44.054
♪♪

08:45.775 --> 08:47.731
Do you see a Wi-Fi password, huh?

08:47.819 --> 08:50.151
- Oh, Jack. Would you just relax?
- I will. I will.

08:50.238 --> 08:54.356
I just... I wanted to send a couple
of emails first and then...

08:54.451 --> 08:56.191
I will relax.

09:04.878 --> 09:06.834
- Hmm.
- Huh?

09:06.921 --> 09:08.121
Still high.

09:08.173 --> 09:11.791
- What?
- My levels. Still high from the travel.

09:11.885 --> 09:13.125
Oh, right.

09:13.219 --> 09:16.211
♪♪

09:36.993 --> 09:39.200
- It's beautiful.
- It really is.

09:40.622 --> 09:42.738
No, you are.

09:42.832 --> 09:45.039
- You're always beautiful.
- Jack.

09:48.004 --> 09:49.960
- Ooh.
- Ugh.

09:50.048 --> 09:51.163
Oh, my god, wait.

09:51.257 --> 09:52.747
Are we all sharing?

09:54.219 --> 09:56.881
- I thought we'd get our own rooms.
- You think I'm happy about it?

09:56.971 --> 09:59.337
- This is not cool.
- Fucking Jack.

09:59.432 --> 10:01.172
He doesn't even get us our own rooms.

10:01.267 --> 10:02.382
Stop calling him Jack.

10:03.812 --> 10:05.652
Why don't you call him dad
anymore? It's weird.

10:07.440 --> 10:10.147
Well, you guys can fight over the cot.

10:10.235 --> 10:11.896
No, Noah.

10:11.986 --> 10:14.272
I'm not sleeping over there.

10:14.364 --> 10:16.104
When I was a little girl,

10:16.199 --> 10:19.862
I had this book about Africa,
and this mountain was on the cover of it.

10:19.953 --> 10:24.322
And I used to stare at it for hours,
just wishing I was there.

10:24.415 --> 10:27.157
And now I'm finally here.
I just can't believe it.

10:31.422 --> 10:35.210
Hey, I'm sorry. I'm sorry if I've been...

10:35.301 --> 10:36.632
An asshole?

10:36.719 --> 10:40.712
I was gonna say distant.
But asshole works, yeah.

10:40.807 --> 10:43.327
It's all right, Jack. I know... I can tell
you've got a lot on your mind.

10:43.351 --> 10:44.932
You know, you could share.

10:47.438 --> 10:49.599
I just want the last family vacation

10:49.691 --> 10:52.603
before Zoe goes off to college
to be special.

10:53.903 --> 10:56.485
If she goes off to college.
You heard her, Jack.

10:57.782 --> 10:59.693
She's gonna go to college.

10:59.784 --> 11:02.471
Who drops out of mit to work in a vegan
coffee shop, for crying out loud?

11:02.495 --> 11:04.827
Is she gonna throw her life away?

11:04.914 --> 11:08.657
Well, I spent seven years in medical
school and haven't worked in 15.

11:08.751 --> 11:10.742
She wants to find herself.

11:10.837 --> 11:13.169
She can find herself after college.

11:13.256 --> 11:14.536
You know... you know what it is?

11:14.591 --> 11:17.754
It's that boyfriend of hers.
That's who's doing this.

11:17.844 --> 11:20.677
I mean, why is he even here, huh?

11:20.763 --> 11:24.176
You want Zoe, you get Billy.
That's young love.

11:24.267 --> 11:26.223
Yeah, he's not that young.

11:26.311 --> 11:27.676
Same age difference as we were.

11:27.770 --> 11:31.433
Yeah. But you didn't make me
cut all my hair off, quit college.

11:31.524 --> 11:33.480
You never had long hair.

11:35.945 --> 11:37.856
Look, he's a nice kid.

11:37.947 --> 11:40.029
He really likes Zoe. I like him.

11:41.117 --> 11:42.653
Yeah.

11:42.744 --> 11:44.359
You don't have to pay for him.

11:44.454 --> 11:46.536
Gosh, can you just relax, Jack?

11:47.582 --> 11:48.582
Relax.

11:54.214 --> 11:55.420
Shoot.

12:03.890 --> 12:06.632
I stink. I'm gonna have a shower.

12:06.726 --> 12:09.718
♪♪

12:33.711 --> 12:35.542
Lots of frogs.

12:35.630 --> 12:39.214
- Oh, remember that little frog I had?
- Ice cream?

12:39.300 --> 12:41.256
Oh, yeah. What happened to him?

12:41.344 --> 12:42.744
I put him in my pocket and he died.

12:42.804 --> 12:44.669
- Jesus, Noah.
- I didn't mean to.

12:44.764 --> 12:46.880
Oh, little guy.

12:49.560 --> 12:51.175
I found you.

12:53.022 --> 12:55.809
- Oh, my god. Oh...
- Do you know what this is?

12:57.360 --> 13:00.443
- Grass?
- No, my friend. Not grass.

13:00.530 --> 13:04.193
- This... is salvia.
- Salvia.

13:04.284 --> 13:06.445
Also known as lady Sally.

13:06.536 --> 13:09.699
Used by many for its analgesic
and anti-spasmodic properties.

13:09.789 --> 13:11.700
But most importantly,
it gets you high as fuck.

13:11.791 --> 13:13.201
I'm sure it's just a shrub.

13:13.293 --> 13:16.501
Guess we'll find out in, what?

13:16.587 --> 13:18.578
Twenty minutes?

13:18.673 --> 13:20.413
- Zoe!
- What?

13:20.508 --> 13:22.499
We're like 100 miles from a hospital.

13:22.593 --> 13:25.756
Oh, my god. You sound like Jack. Ugh.

13:25.847 --> 13:28.409
You know, that actually makes him
really upset, when you call him that.

13:28.433 --> 13:29.798
He can take it. It's fine.

13:31.394 --> 13:33.259
Come on, Zoe.

13:33.354 --> 13:36.312
I'm actually going to do a workout
with dad before dinner,

13:36.399 --> 13:39.766
doing like an African circuit thing...

13:39.861 --> 13:40.941
Okay.

13:44.407 --> 13:46.068
You've been fired?

13:47.702 --> 13:50.535
You looked... you looked at my phone?

13:50.621 --> 13:52.433
- That's an invasion of my...
- Don't you dare, Jack.

13:52.457 --> 13:54.243
Give me my phone. Give me my...

13:54.334 --> 13:56.450
- What happened?
- Nothing. I wasn't fired.

13:56.544 --> 13:57.813
It was... it's administrative leave.

13:57.837 --> 13:59.498
- Jack! Stop it!
- Nothing happened. Okay?

13:59.589 --> 14:00.629
- What happened?
- Nothing.

14:00.673 --> 14:03.881
There was a small problem
with the Dakota pipeline and it...

14:07.055 --> 14:08.340
It's standard protocol...

14:09.432 --> 14:12.299
To put the project manager
on administrative leave

14:12.393 --> 14:13.428
while they clean it up.

14:13.519 --> 14:15.555
Clean it up? What?

14:15.646 --> 14:17.432
Was there a spill?

14:17.523 --> 14:20.560
A little bit. It was handled.
I mean, maybe a little late.

14:20.651 --> 14:22.629
Well, how... how bad was it?
Why didn't you tell me?

14:22.653 --> 14:26.441
I did... I didn't tell you because I wanted
you to enjoy this vacation, okay?

14:26.532 --> 14:28.113
God knows it costs enough.

14:29.494 --> 14:30.984
Wait...

14:31.079 --> 14:33.786
Do we have to worry
about money now? I...

14:34.957 --> 14:36.101
Things could get a little tight

14:36.125 --> 14:38.228
and we might need to tighten our belts
7 little after this.

14:38.252 --> 14:39.833
- Yeah.
- Are you going to be fired?

14:39.921 --> 14:41.357
No, I'm not going to be fired. Okay?

14:41.381 --> 14:44.748
No, it's not like that.
I... I don't think so.

14:44.842 --> 14:48.175
I'll go back as soon as they sort it out.
Can I please have my phone?

14:54.352 --> 14:55.933
Wait, Billy. Whoa, whoa, whoa.

14:57.438 --> 15:00.430
Wow. What is this place?

15:00.525 --> 15:02.265
So cool.

15:04.028 --> 15:05.893
Wait, Billy, look. Look at the milky way.

15:06.906 --> 15:09.488
Oh, my god. It's so cool.

15:09.575 --> 15:12.237
You see this? Oh.

15:12.328 --> 15:14.364
- Hey, baby?
- What?

15:14.455 --> 15:16.286
- You're the starlight queen.
- Hmm.

15:22.296 --> 15:23.877
Oh, thank you.

15:30.596 --> 15:34.180
That was so cool.
Hey, come dance!

15:34.267 --> 15:37.009
Come on. Come and dance.

15:37.103 --> 15:38.343
No? Okay.

15:43.568 --> 15:45.058
Let's go. Come on.

15:45.153 --> 15:48.020
Seven, eight, nine. And now clap it out.

15:48.114 --> 15:50.901
One, two, three.
More pushups, let's go.

15:50.992 --> 15:53.199
- Five, six, seven.
- Oh, geez, dad.

15:53.286 --> 15:54.776
Come on, come on.
Hey, seven, seven.

15:54.871 --> 15:57.328
- Slow. Come on.
- Okay.

15:57.415 --> 15:59.685
- Hey, come on. One more set.
- We've been going for like 10 minutes.

15:59.709 --> 16:01.791
- Jesus.
- All right.

16:01.878 --> 16:03.709
All right, let's go. Okay,
you get a break.

16:03.796 --> 16:05.274
- You get 30 seconds. Let's go.
- Dad...

16:05.298 --> 16:06.333
Huh?

16:06.424 --> 16:08.085
- Are you okay?
- Yeah, I'm fine.

16:09.093 --> 16:11.196
- You and mom got in a fight again.
- Twenty-five... no, no, we're fine.

16:11.220 --> 16:14.007
Everything's good. We...
We're fine.

16:14.098 --> 16:16.635
I promise. How's your, uh, relationship?

16:16.726 --> 16:18.466
How's your, uh...

16:20.021 --> 16:21.136
- Sam?
- How's Sam?

16:22.773 --> 16:26.436
You don't have to ask.
I know you don't... want to.

16:27.695 --> 16:29.811
No. I do. I do.

16:29.906 --> 16:31.396
I want to know. How...

16:31.491 --> 16:32.697
How is he?

16:34.619 --> 16:35.904
Fine?

16:35.995 --> 16:38.111
He's not distracting you, is he?

16:38.206 --> 16:41.039
- No, he's not distracting me.
- All right.

16:43.252 --> 16:45.117
It's just, you know, it's...

16:46.506 --> 16:49.168
Something that your coach said.

16:49.258 --> 16:50.944
- What?
- He was just checking if you were okay.

16:50.968 --> 16:53.550
I mean, what with all
the doctor's appointments

16:53.638 --> 16:55.674
that you've been going
to over the last few weeks.

16:55.765 --> 16:59.553
The ones that conveniently
fall between the hours of 6 and 8 P.M.

16:59.644 --> 17:02.351
Right in the middle of practice?

17:02.438 --> 17:05.601
I mean, from where I'm standing,
this thing is distracting you.

17:05.691 --> 17:08.773
- No. Sam is not a thing.
- You know what I'm saying.

17:08.861 --> 17:11.694
Yes, I do know what you're saying.
You wish that Sam was my girlfriend.

17:11.781 --> 17:13.692
- But he's not. He's my boy...
- That's not...

17:13.782 --> 17:15.272
Hey!

17:15.367 --> 17:17.358
- What?
- I don't know. I don't know. But...

17:18.663 --> 17:19.782
- What is it?
- I don't know.

17:22.750 --> 17:24.353
- What the hell happened?
- It was a hyena.

17:24.377 --> 17:25.521
He just walked right up here.

17:25.545 --> 17:27.105
- Ran right up here.
- Well, is... is everyone okay?

17:27.128 --> 17:28.440
- Everyone's fine.
- You okay? You okay?

17:28.464 --> 17:30.250
- Yeah. Yeah.
- It came...

17:30.341 --> 17:31.706
It came creeping out of the trees.

17:36.806 --> 17:38.512
Oh, wow. Yeah, look at him.

17:38.599 --> 17:40.880
- He's right there.
- Yeah, he's right there. You see him?

17:44.105 --> 17:46.096
Did you see that mangy-looking
dog-like thing?

17:46.190 --> 17:48.101
Oh, I thought he was pretty handsome.

17:48.192 --> 17:51.650
He was just looking for food.
No harm, everyone.

17:51.737 --> 17:53.443
- Hey, are you okay?
- It's a hyena, Noah.

17:53.531 --> 17:57.649
My god. But they're...
They're kind of dangerous, right?

17:57.743 --> 18:01.156
Well, they're scavengers, bro.
Nature's trash cans, right?

18:01.247 --> 18:04.956
That's true, Billy.
But one alone is just harmless.

18:05.042 --> 18:08.876
But if they're in a group, they're
very dangerous. They can even kill a lion.

18:10.131 --> 18:11.491
- Okay.
- When found alone,

18:11.549 --> 18:12.834
this can do the magic.

18:12.925 --> 18:14.711
It's all you need, really.

18:14.802 --> 18:15.802
That's okay.

18:15.886 --> 18:18.343
- Just go back to having fun.
- You know, uh,

18:18.431 --> 18:21.013
no hyenas in bora bora.

18:22.768 --> 18:23.768
Come on.

18:31.235 --> 18:32.441
Oh, thank you.

18:59.930 --> 19:02.200
- Jack, can you put that away?
- Hmm? Yeah, yeah.

19:02.224 --> 19:04.715
- Good morning.
- Morning, honey.

19:04.810 --> 19:06.095
Morning, sweetheart.

19:08.272 --> 19:10.183
- So cool, Jack.
- What?

19:10.274 --> 19:12.514
Oh, honey, come here. Let me get that.

19:14.528 --> 19:17.110
Mom. Why so early?

19:17.198 --> 19:20.440
Adventure begins early, honey.
Have some coffee, you'll wake up.

19:20.534 --> 19:22.525
