for the extras now...

20:26.642 --> 20:28.849
And how much would that be?

20:30.104 --> 20:33.016
Great news.
We get to do our own safari today.

20:34.024 --> 20:35.434
- What?
- Yeah, yeah.

20:35.526 --> 20:37.357
Our friend Lucas back there,
he just told me

20:37.445 --> 20:39.686
if we want the best experience possible,

20:39.780 --> 20:41.941
we gotta go into the park on our own.

20:42.950 --> 20:44.281
That... doesn't sound...

20:44.368 --> 20:45.904
- Right.
- It is. It is.

20:45.995 --> 20:47.635
- Don't we need a guard?
- Yeah, and guns.

20:47.663 --> 20:49.743
No, no, no, all that stuff
is just fluff. It's extra.

20:49.790 --> 20:53.578
It's just one big safari park in there.
Besides, we have our van and our map.

20:53.669 --> 20:55.500
And we get to do it together.
It'll be fun.

20:55.588 --> 20:59.001
Our big five finds their big five, right?

20:59.091 --> 21:01.082
Yeah.

21:01.177 --> 21:03.177
Prrrr. Right. Come on.
Let's go. Let's go. Come on.

21:07.808 --> 21:10.766
- Bye. Have fun.
- Bye-bye. Have a good one.

21:10.853 --> 21:12.693
- We have to try. Let's see.
- One, two, three.

21:14.482 --> 21:16.473
- Oh, that's great, guys.
- Cool.

21:16.567 --> 21:18.273
This is gonna work out just fine.

21:18.360 --> 21:21.648
Plastic water bottles, Jack?
They have glass ones here.

21:21.739 --> 21:23.650
Here they actually care
about the environment.

21:23.741 --> 21:26.483
Yeah, you know, the main product
of the water bottle industry

21:26.577 --> 21:28.408
is plastic, not water, Jack.

21:28.496 --> 21:30.282
- Excuse me. Excuse me.
- Did you know that?

21:30.372 --> 21:31.953
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

21:32.041 --> 21:34.407
- Did you know that, honey?
- It's true, honey.

21:34.502 --> 21:36.208
Too much plastic in the world.

21:36.295 --> 21:37.876
Okay. Are we good to go?

21:37.963 --> 21:39.794
- Yeah. Got your Insulin?
- Yes, I do.

21:40.966 --> 21:42.027
- Yeah.
- Let's do it!

21:42.051 --> 21:44.087
All right, here we go.

21:44.178 --> 21:45.906
- Let's do this.
- Oh, shit. I forgot my sunglasses.

21:45.930 --> 21:47.650
That's... it's gonna be what it's gonna be.

21:47.723 --> 21:49.805
- Oh... are you sure?
- It's fine.

21:49.892 --> 21:51.703
"Do not get out
of your vehicle at any time."

21:51.727 --> 21:54.218
- Oh, this is cool.
- "Do not exceed 30 km/h."

21:54.313 --> 21:56.349
- "Do not litter."
- Here we are.

21:56.440 --> 21:57.850
- Okay.
- Okay.

21:57.942 --> 22:00.433
- Zoe, are you seeing this?
- Wow, wow, wow.

22:00.528 --> 22:02.297
- I'm so excited.
- I can't believe it.

22:02.321 --> 22:04.007
- Okay. I'm a little bit excited.
- How are you?

22:04.031 --> 22:07.114
Oh, she's gonna try
and sell you something, mom.

22:07.201 --> 22:09.012
They're so pretty!
Zoe, are you seeing this?

22:09.036 --> 22:11.448
No. Mom. They're like 20 bucks.

22:11.539 --> 22:13.099
- Hi there, hi. Good morning.
- Hello. How are you, sir?

22:13.123 --> 22:15.614
Hi, there. Hi.
Good morning. Ah, jambo.

22:15.709 --> 22:17.062
- That one was late.
- Mom, you gotta get one.

22:17.086 --> 22:19.498
- Welcome to Amboseli.
- Please, please.

22:19.588 --> 22:23.251
- Did you bring Kenyan money?
- They're beautiful!

22:23.342 --> 22:25.879
- They look like this.
- What are you doing?

22:25.970 --> 22:27.531
- What are you doing?
- Shh. Jack, come on.

22:27.555 --> 22:30.388
- Did you bring...
- We don't need a belt.

22:30.474 --> 22:32.114
Why you need a belt?
They're so beautiful!

22:32.142 --> 22:34.679
- Hi!
- Look, it's real official-looking.

22:34.770 --> 22:37.603
- Hey, what's going on?
- What do we need a belt for?

22:37.690 --> 22:39.000
Don't... don't waste our money, honey.

22:39.024 --> 22:41.356
- They're made here.
- Made... made here. Made in China.

22:41.443 --> 22:43.104
- Jack...
- Oh, no, thanks.

22:43.195 --> 22:47.154
- Wow. What's going on over there?
- They caught more poachers.

22:47.241 --> 22:49.441
I thought they said poaching
wasn't really a thing here.

22:49.493 --> 22:50.679
They don't look like poachers.

22:50.703 --> 22:52.614
And what are poachers
supposed to look like?

22:52.705 --> 22:53.705
Not tourists.

22:53.789 --> 22:56.826
Those bastards kill, like,
1,000 rhinos a year.

22:56.917 --> 23:00.409
- Holy shit. That's three rhinos a day.
- That's quick math, hon.

23:00.504 --> 23:01.565
Wait, so you don't think
we'll see a rhino?

23:01.589 --> 23:03.295
You don't have to sound too shocked, Jack.

23:03.382 --> 23:04.997
Nah, sorry, Mrs. H.

23:05.092 --> 23:07.959
They're as rare as pink
and fluffy unicorn shit.

23:08.053 --> 23:11.545
- Hey, excuse me. Excuse me. Do you mind?
- One minute. Please wait.

23:11.640 --> 23:13.255
Excuse me, sir. Do you mind if...

23:13.350 --> 23:14.995
Do you mind if we just go through?

23:15.019 --> 23:17.476
- Oh, my god.
- Holy shit.

23:20.065 --> 23:22.252
Jack. Jack, what are you doing?

23:22.276 --> 23:23.732
You wanna go on a safari?

23:23.819 --> 23:25.525
I'm gonna take you on a gosh darn safari.

23:25.613 --> 23:28.150
Don't... don't do it. Jack!
Jack! Jack!

23:28.240 --> 23:29.901
Hold on! You haven't paid!

23:29.992 --> 23:32.278
You haven't paid! Come back here!

23:33.913 --> 23:35.949
Sometimes
you have to break the rules.

23:36.040 --> 23:37.826
We'll pay you when we come out.

23:37.917 --> 23:40.909
♪♪

24:00.940 --> 24:04.524
Are these the right roads?
I don't see any animals.

24:06.654 --> 24:09.646
We did come to the right place. Right?

24:10.866 --> 24:14.233
- There's not much here, is there?
- Well, you know, it's not a zoo.

24:14.328 --> 24:17.240
I mean, they're here.
They're just not close.

24:17.331 --> 24:20.323
♪♪

24:51.991 --> 24:54.027
- Jack.
- What?

24:54.118 --> 24:55.278
What are you doing?

24:56.453 --> 24:59.445
- We're not allowed that way.
- I bet it loops back to the main road.

24:59.540 --> 25:01.434
- What makes you think that?
- You should check the map.

25:01.458 --> 25:02.573
There's no sign.

25:02.668 --> 25:06.502
Look, your mom wants to see a rhino.
I'm gonna find her a rhino.

25:06.588 --> 25:08.624
This... I will make happen.

25:08.716 --> 25:11.332
- All about breaking the rules today, huh?
- Looks like it.

25:18.225 --> 25:20.967
Off-road adventure.

25:21.061 --> 25:22.821
All right. Watch your head.
Watch your heads.

25:24.523 --> 25:26.104
Oh. Oh.

25:27.484 --> 25:28.724
All right. Here we go.

25:28.819 --> 25:31.811
♪♪

25:33.782 --> 25:35.113
Any water back there, guys?

25:35.200 --> 25:37.111
- Yeah.
- Here you go.

25:37.202 --> 25:39.033
- Here you go, Mrs. H.
- Thank you.

25:40.831 --> 25:44.665
Hang on. I spy with my little eye...

25:45.669 --> 25:48.160
Something beginning with... holy shit.

25:48.255 --> 25:50.997
I don't think
that's how the game works, Billy.

25:51.091 --> 25:52.501
No, no. Over there.

25:53.844 --> 25:56.210
No, no, no. Over there. Over there.

25:56.305 --> 25:57.465
- Where?
- There.

25:57.556 --> 25:58.716
What?

25:58.807 --> 26:03.096
The dead thing in the tree right there.

26:03.187 --> 26:05.052
- Ugh.
- What is that, a deer?

26:05.147 --> 26:07.333
- Maybe an antelope or something?
- How did it even get up there?

26:07.357 --> 26:09.143
- Jump?
- And get stuck?

26:09.234 --> 26:11.441
- Can they climb?
- No, I don't think so.

26:11.528 --> 26:12.358
Geez.

26:12.446 --> 26:15.279
That's gross. Billy, that's gross.

26:15.365 --> 26:16.605
- Gross?
- It's dead.

26:16.700 --> 26:19.988
It's... it's wildlife.
There's flies there. They're alive.

26:22.664 --> 26:24.029
Billy!

26:24.124 --> 26:26.331
All right, hold on. Hold on.

26:28.879 --> 26:29.981
Wait, wait. Can I get a picture?

26:30.005 --> 26:32.747
- No, you can't get a picture, Noah.
- Ew. Are you a serial killer?

26:32.841 --> 26:34.502
- What?
- Don't take a picture of that.

26:34.593 --> 26:36.112
We're not gonna see
another animal in a tree.

26:36.136 --> 26:39.173
I'm sure we will see lots of dead animals.

26:39.264 --> 26:40.424
I'm gonna send it to Sam.

26:43.644 --> 26:45.760
- Dad?
- Yeah, bud.

26:45.854 --> 26:47.719
Can I drive for a bit?

26:47.815 --> 26:50.602
Um... well, it's a stick.

26:50.692 --> 26:52.102
I can drive a stick.

26:53.320 --> 26:55.840
I don't know, pal. I don't think
the insurance will cover you again.

26:55.864 --> 26:58.526
What? You said you were
all about breaking the rules today.

26:58.617 --> 27:01.359
Come on, Jack. Let him drive.

27:01.453 --> 27:03.389
Okay, all right. All right, bud.
Yeah, you can drive.

27:03.413 --> 27:05.725
- Well, that's us dead.
- I'm actually a really good driver.

27:05.749 --> 27:08.081
I think the back of dad's Porsche
would disagree with that.

27:08.168 --> 27:10.534
That was not my fault. I buffed it out.

27:10.629 --> 27:13.371
- At least I have a license.
- Hey, I can drive.

27:13.465 --> 27:14.665
- She can drive.
- I can drive.

27:14.716 --> 27:16.152
Not according to the state of California.

27:16.176 --> 27:17.445
- Guys, guys, guys.
- That's just a piece of paper.

27:17.469 --> 27:18.530
- Noah...
- It's actually...

27:18.554 --> 27:19.614
- Come on up here.
- Want to do it here?

27:19.638 --> 27:21.238
- I need my fixin'.
- All right. Hold on.

27:24.268 --> 27:25.348
- All right.
- Get my fix.

27:25.435 --> 27:26.871
- You're welcome.
- Hey, mom.

27:26.895 --> 27:29.227
All right. Hop up here, bud.

27:29.314 --> 27:30.895
There you go.

27:30.983 --> 27:32.644
All right, big guy.
There you go. Okay.

27:32.734 --> 27:33.962
All right. No more than 10, okay?

27:33.986 --> 27:36.272
- What? That's walking.
- Do it.

27:36.363 --> 27:38.216
- Come on, Noah. Put your feet on the gas.
- No. 20.

27:38.240 --> 27:40.526
- Twenty. No. No.
- Shut up, okay?

27:40.617 --> 27:42.804
Both both feet down, right.
Clutch all the way to the floor.

27:42.828 --> 27:44.784
Over and up.

27:44.872 --> 27:46.954
Now, a little bit of gas.
Let go of that clutch.

27:49.084 --> 27:51.187
- That's okay. That's okay.
- Oh, wow. Such a good driver.

27:51.211 --> 27:52.981
- Way to go, Noah.
- Such a good driver.

27:58.510 --> 27:59.590
Yeah, there we go.

28:01.054 --> 28:03.420
♪♪

28:03.515 --> 28:05.801
Now we're gonna see some wildlife.

28:09.438 --> 28:11.019
- We don't want any more zebra.
- Yeah.

28:11.106 --> 28:13.188
- Okay?
- Are we bored with zebra?

28:13.275 --> 28:14.355
Gosh, I can't believe...

28:16.486 --> 28:19.478
♪♪

28:23.493 --> 28:25.529
Yeah. Whoever thought
we'd be bored by a zebra.

28:25.621 --> 28:28.658
- Bored by zebras. Right?
- Bored by zebras, that's right.

28:28.749 --> 28:30.990
- That is amazing. Billy, Zoe, not again.
- Oh, my!

28:32.502 --> 28:36.245
- What the fuck, Noah?
- Oh, my... gosh.

28:37.257 --> 28:40.294
♪♪

28:40.385 --> 28:41.841
- Oh, wow.
- Got you a rhino, baby.

28:41.929 --> 28:45.387
Oh, yes, you did, baby.
This is incredible.

28:46.975 --> 28:48.761
Wow. It's gorgeous.

28:51.939 --> 28:54.555
Wow!

28:54.650 --> 28:56.461
Hey, guys, can we get a little closer?
Just a little bit?

28:56.485 --> 28:57.850
- Can I?
- Please?

28:57.945 --> 29:00.402
Yeah, yeah, go ahead.
Just some nice...

29:00.489 --> 29:03.401
Oh, wow. This is unbelievable.

29:03.492 --> 29:04.607
Just a little... ah!

29:06.119 --> 29:10.032
Giant animal with a spike on its face.
What could possibly go wrong?

29:10.123 --> 29:11.533
Mom, are you getting the picture?

29:11.625 --> 29:13.866
I mean, never in my wildest dreams.

29:13.961 --> 29:15.480
Are you seeing...

29:15.504 --> 29:16.710
Oh, wow.

29:19.549 --> 29:21.380
Oh, wow. Zoe, look at this. Is this...

29:21.468 --> 29:24.835
- Is that a baby? Look, is that a baby?
- Oh, my god.

29:24.930 --> 29:27.763
- That is so cute.
- Hi! Look at the baby.

29:27.849 --> 29:30.431
Wait, we shouldn't be getting
between them. Right?

29:30.519 --> 29:33.352
Yeah, I can't believe I'm saying this,
but I agree with you, Billy.

29:33.438 --> 29:34.749
- Back it up just a bit.
- Wait, I'm not...

29:34.773 --> 29:36.125
Lauren, Lauren.
Would you get down, honey?

29:36.149 --> 29:37.418
I'm not good at reversing.

29:37.442 --> 29:39.587
- Is that in reverse?
- That's in reverse. There you go.

29:39.611 --> 29:40.838
Oh, my god. Noah, back it up.

29:40.862 --> 29:42.648
Noah, back it up!

29:42.739 --> 29:44.821
- It's okay.
- I'm sorry. Sorry, okay?

29:46.034 --> 29:48.446
Oh, my gosh. Stop it. Noah!

29:48.537 --> 29:50.243
I'm not good at reversing, I'm sorry.

29:50.330 --> 29:52.330
- Slowly. There you go.
- Oh, my gosh. Oh, my gosh.

29:53.417 --> 29:54.857
- Oh, my god! Dad.
- No, you're okay.

30:10.517 --> 30:12.599
Drive! Jack, drive!

30:15.814 --> 30:16.974
Drive!

30:19.901 --> 30:22.984
Oh, oh, my gosh. Oh, my gosh.
It's okay, it's okay.

30:23.071 --> 30:25.403
She's done. She's done.
She's not done. She's not done.

30:31.079 --> 30:32.944
- Jack!
- She gone?

30:36.752 --> 30:37.867
No! No! No!

30:37.961 --> 30:39.622
♪♪

30:54.478 --> 30:57.766
Everybody okay? Noah. Zoe.

30:57.856 --> 31:00.893
- Oh, fuck!
- She's gone.

31:00.984 --> 31:02.474
She's gone. She's gone. She's gone.

31:02.569 --> 31:03.900
Are you okay?

31:03.987 --> 31:05.477
She's gone.
She's gone. She's gone.

31:05.572 --> 31:06.982
She's gone, Jack.

31:07.074 --> 31:09.190
You got... you got tagged.

31:09.284 --> 31:11.554
- Did it hit the femoral?
- No, it did not hit the femoral.

31:11.578 --> 31:12.909
If it did, you'd be dead by now.

31:12.996 --> 31:14.987
But you know what?
You're bleeding badly.

31:15.082 --> 31:16.618
You guys okay? Is everyone okay?

31:16.708 --> 31:19.290
I'll be right there, Zoe. Hang in there.

31:19.378 --> 31:21.414
- You... all right.
- Okay.

31:21.505 --> 31:22.995
Okay, okay.

31:23.090 --> 31:24.375
Zoe?

31:24.466 --> 31:26.252
Yeah, yeah.
Just stop touching it.

31:26.343 --> 31:28.004
Honey, are you okay, baby?

31:28.095 --> 31:29.380
Okay.

31:29.471 --> 31:31.632
Put all your weight on that.

31:31.723 --> 31:33.714
- Okay. That's great.
- All right. Okay.

31:33.809 --> 31:35.515
- My head...
- Are you okay?

31:37.145 --> 31:38.790
- Noah? Are you okay, bud?
- There's so much blood.

31:38.814 --> 31:40.350
- I'm all right, dad.
- So much blood.

31:40.440 --> 31:41.555
I think-I think it's bad.

31:41.650 --> 31:44.983
Mom... mom...

31:45.070 --> 31:46.480
Mom, what's happening?

31:46.571 --> 31:47.686
Are you all right, Noah?

31:47.781 --> 31:49.612
Are you okay? Okay. All right.

31:49.699 --> 31:51.690
- Okay, Zoe, here I come.
- Mom, it's broken.

31:51.785 --> 31:53.513
It might not be broken.
It might be dislocated.

31:53.537 --> 31:55.640
- It's broken. I know it's broken.
- Let me see. Let me see.

31:55.664 --> 31:57.392
- Dad, what happened?
- Fucking thing off me!

31:57.416 --> 31:59.907
- Okay. All right.
- Is it broken?

32:00.001 --> 32:02.001
Remember what happened
when you fell off your bike?

32:02.045 --> 32:03.356
Yeah. I remember how much it hurt.

32:03.380 --> 32:04.836
Okay, I remember how brave you were.

32:04.923 --> 32:06.288
No. I wasn't brave. I'm not, mom.

32:06.383 --> 32:07.793
Brace it from behind. There we go.

32:08.844 --> 32:10.334
Oh, fuck!

32:15.517 --> 32:17.161
I'm fine. I'm fine. Jack?

32:17.185 --> 32:18.550
Ah, yeah, yeah.

32:18.645 --> 32:20.727
- Okay.
- Thank you. Okay.

32:20.814 --> 32:22.454
Baby, I would
have done the same.

32:23.567 --> 32:26.809
- Here.
- That's okay. It's okay.

32:26.903 --> 32:29.184
- You guys all right?
- Are you okay, Zoe?

32:30.699 --> 32:32.860
If I would've...
If I would've just backed up...

32:32.951 --> 32:34.429
- Been able to drive fast?
- Faster.

32:34.453 --> 32:35.930
It's done now.
It's done, all right?

32:35.954 --> 32:38.411
- Zoe, lay off.
- Ah, jeez.

32:38.498 --> 32:41.365
Well, let's, uh, let's see
if we can right this thing.

32:41.460 --> 32:42.700
See if it still drives.

32:42.794 --> 32:46.412
